a tha againne an Albainn fada air deireadh air na seòrsaichcan tha agus a bha an rìoghachdan eile , cleas na seann mhusette Fhrangach ( ’ se Pìob Northumberland aon de ghineal na h - ionnstramaid so ) agus a ’ Phìob Eireannach . So beagan mu ’ n phìob á leabhran a chuireadh a mach an 1968 le Comunn Ghalpin ( comunn airson a bhith sgrùdadh eachdraidh ionnstramaidean - ciùil ) ;
“ the Scottish Highland bagpipe [is] basically a straight - forward folk species . . . the other specimens represent more sophisticated types . . . . The Irish Union pipe surpasses all others in sheer musical scope . Chromatic chanter , a chanter capable of staccato and of sounding in the overblown register , some provision for flashes of harmony between the various pipes . . . . Its [the Irish] most singular feature , the ‘ regulator , ’ should be mentioned . . . . To this single regulator two others were added in the 19th century , all three being struck simultaneously to make full chords . ”
Chan eil duine a chuala an ceòl aig MacPeake is a Mhac — a ’ seinn is a ’ pìobaireachd an co - sheirm — nach aontaich leis a ’ mholadh so .
